    How does Amazon calculate star ratings?
    Amazon calculates a product’s star ratings based on a machine learned model instead of a raw data average. The model takes into account factors including the age of a rating, whether the ratings are from verified purchasers, and factors that establish reviewer trustworthiness.

    thay
    4.0 out of 5 stars Great, but need internal wall clearance
    Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2017
    Item Package Quantity: 1Verified Purchase
    This works fine, but I have one minor issue with it.
    It's switch panel is really very flat! That's great, but for an RV installation with any less than perfect install conditions the flat panel means the switch housing is recessed further into the wall. If you have any insulation you're going to have to pretty much cut it out straight to the siding to get this guy to fit in a 2" wall with the switch housing and 12v wires plugged into the back. This would be great if it were elevated about 1/4" or so.
    If you have a clear hole you'll be good to go, but I'm going to consider building a base for it, maybe 2 squares of cut aluminum sheet as a backing plate to pull it out of the wall a bit or build a small 1/4" wood base (can always paint it a trim color around edge)
    I mean, it's what I ordered, but I kind of expected the switch housing to be a little flatter since it doesn't stick part of the way out of the wall like the original switches did (1/2" extrusion)

    5.0 out of 5 stars Sleek beautiful, easy to install!
    Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2016
    Item Package Quantity: 1Verified Purchase
    Excellent replacement for bulky and ugly brown switchplate factory installed in my RV. Sleek, low profile hugs the wall and does not stick out. I was thinking I would have to keep the old plastic housing, but this was unnecessary. I mounted this directly on the RV kitchen wall with two screws that fit exactly into the old holes. In the back, the DC wires plugged right into the slots as usual. Ceiling light fixture works without issues. Very pleased with the look and quality feel, and will be replacing every other ugly plate I can find. Only wish this came in a Satin or Brushed Nickel instead of polished chrome, but that is minor. Still matches the silver on my nickle cabinet handles. Strongly recommend.
